{{wikipedia}}
==English==
===Noun===
{{en-noun|tautologies|-}}

# {{cattag|linguistics|uncountable}} [[redundant]] use of words
#: ''It is '''tautology''' to say, "a big large fish".''
# {{cattag|linguistics|countable}} An expression that features tautology.
# {{cattag|logic|countable}} A [[statement]] that is true for all [[value]]s of its [[variable]]s
#: ''Given a Boolean A, "A OR (NOT A)" is a '''tautology'''.''

====Antonyms====
*(''linguistics: expression''): [[contradiction in terms]]
*(''in logic''): [[contradiction]]

